ope in the face of crises  dec  david miliband president and chief executive officer of the international rescue committee irc discusses his career in public service and the irc’s mission to provide relief and development operations in more than  countries around the world watch videos cardinal timothy dolan finding faith in a modern world  nov  cardinal timothy dolan archbishop of new york discusses leadership and the evolution of the catholic church watch video ray kelly the intersection of local and international security  nov  former new york city police department nypd commissioner ray kelly discusses his year career in public service and the intersection of local and international security watch videos linda rottenberg developing high impact entrepreneurs  oct  linda rottenberg cofounder and ceo of nonprofit organization endeavor which identifies and supports highimpact entrepreneurs in developing countries to promote longterm economic growth discusses the concept of entrepreneurship and the power of taking risks watch videos cristián samper protecting wildlife and wild places  oct  dr cristián samper president and chief executive officer of the wildlife conservation society wcs discusses the importance of publicprivate partnerships including that between wcs and goldman sachs to create the karukinka natural park in tierra del fuego chile watch video general stan mcchrystal effecting change through public service  oct  general stan mcchrystal former commander of the united states armed forces afghanistan and founder of the aspen institute’s franklin project discusses the current geopolitical landscape and the importance of public service watch video lauren bush lauren alleviating world hunger through social entrepreneurship  sep  lauren bush lauren founder creative director and chief executive officer of feed projects discusses social entrepreneurship and world hunger watch videos cherie blair investing in women entrepreneurs  sep  barrister and philanthropist