s try to find the white space and create something new def jam recordings cofounder russell simmons discusses innovation and living a balanced life watch video panel storytelling as an agent of global change  oct  storytelling is fundamental to the mission of the national geographic society which leverages it to impact global change the national geographic society panelists share their perspectives on storytelling and how science and exploration work to help readers understand the economic and social change it can create watch video neil berg broadway behind the curtain  oct  composer lyricist and producer neil berg has produced hundreds of concerts across the world at a talks at gs session at goldman sachs in new york berg discusses his decadeslong career and creative process as well as the business of broadway learn more ross kemp documenting extreme stories  oct  actor and awardwinning documentary maker ross kemp’s investigative journalism series covers a range of extreme situations from gang culture to conflict zones to border standoffs during a talks at gs session kemp discussed the experience of capturing compelling stories in dangerous situations watch video bob colacello the intersection of culture politics and media  aug  during his more than year career journalist and vanity fair special correspondent bob colacello has profiled more than  iconic figures the former editor of andy warholfounded interview magazine discusses the intersection of culture politics and media watch video ava duvernay the making of selma  jul   marks the th anniversary of the passage of the voting rights act of  director ava duvernay discussed her film selma which chronicles the historic civil rights marches from selma to montgomery in  learn more danny meyer the business of hospitality  jun  since opening his first restaurant in  restaurateur danny meyer has become a fixture on the new york city dining scene the chief executive officer of union square hospitality group discusses th